MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

93-1939. State v. Hayward.

Summit County, No. 16313. This cause is pending before the court on the filing of a motion for leave to appeal from the Court of Appeals for Summit County and as a claimed appeal as of right from said court. Upon consideration of appellant’s application for dismissal,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that said application be, and the same is hereby, granted, effective January 12, 1994.

ACCORDINGLY, IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.
